    <h2>The problem with AIM newsflow</h2>

    <p>AIM generates thousands of regulatory announcements every year.</p>
    <p>Most are administrative. Some materially alter valuation.</p>
    <p>In the raw feed, they appear indistinguishable.</p>

    <p><strong>In smaller companies, single announcements can materially alter valuation.</strong></p>

    <p>Investors are forced to manually interpret:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Capital raises and dilution</li>
      <li>Guidance revisions and trading updates</li>
      <li>Contract wins and material customer changes</li>
      <li>Balance sheet and liquidity shifts</li>
      <li>Director dealings and governance changes</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>By the time impact is clear, the market has often already moved.</strong></p>
  </section>

  <!-- SOLUTION -->
  <section aria-label="Solution">
    <h2>How smallcaps.ai brings structure</h2>

